The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Wednesday, September 01, 2004 

 IN THE CITY

 The Japan national team is arriving here on September 7, a day before their pre-World Cup qualifier against India. Two of the Japanese players Shunsuke Nakamura and Atsushi Yanagisawa will be arriving here directly from Italy.

 The IFA announced on Tuesday that the students with uniform, nursery division footballers and coaching centre wards will be given free entry on September 8. Union sports minister Sunil Dutt will be the chief guest.

 Bhaichung Bhutia, who sustained a cartilage damage during the LG Cup in Vietnam, underwent an orthoscopy on his left knee. Bhutia underwent a micro-surgery at a city nursing home under orthopaedic surgeon Dr Debashis Chatterjee.

 Calcutta Deaf and Dumb School got past St Anthony High School 2-1 in an inter-school football tournament match on Sunday.

 The 14-member Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB XI) squad for the Moin-ud Dowla Gold Cup tournament was announced on Tuesday.

 THE SQUAD

 CC amp;FC and Calcutta Police made it to the semi-finals of the All India and South Asia rugby meet at the CC amp;FC on Tuesday. CC amp;FC beat Delhi 26-5 while the policemen edged past Future Hope 7-5.

 AQUATICS: 45th All India railway meet at Subhas Sarobar pool from 8 am.

 RUGBY: All India and South Asia meet at the CC amp;FC from 10 am.




